## 🔒 Security Architecture — The #1 Priority

Since you specifically called out security, here's the complete security model:

### Current Security (Already Built ✅)
```
✅ Supabase RLS — Row-level isolation per user
✅ Rate Limiting — All 6 API routes protected
✅ IDOR Protection — user_id from server session only
✅ Input Validation — Double layer (Zod + SQL CHECK)
✅ Admin RBAC — Email whitelist + service role separation
✅ XSS Protection — React auto-escapes
✅ SQL Injection Protection — Supabase parameterized queries
✅ Credentials in .env — Not committed to git
```

### Security Upgrades Needed for Personal Finance Features

| Layer | What to Add | How |
|-------|-------------|-----|
| **Data at Rest** | AES-256 encryption for sensitive financial data | Supabase Vault or `pgcrypto` extension |
| **Data in Transit** | Already HTTPS via Vercel | ✅ Already done |
| **PII Handling** | Encrypt user's card numbers, bank details | Column-level encryption in PostgreSQL |
| **Audit Logging** | Log every data access for compliance | `audit_logs` table with trigger functions |
| **Session Security** | Shorter JWT expiry + refresh token rotation | Supabase Auth config |
| **API Security** | HMAC request signing for sensitive endpoints | Custom middleware |
| **India Compliance** | DPDP Act 2023 — consent management, data deletion | Consent flow + data purge API |
| **Anomaly Detection** | Flag unusual access patterns | IP + device fingerprinting |

### Security Implementation Plan

```
Phase 1 (Week 1-2):
├── pgcrypto extension for column-level encryption
├── audit_logs table with trigger-based logging
├── Consent management flow (DPDP Act)
├── Data deletion API (Right to Erasure)
└── Enhanced session management

Phase 2 (Week 3-4):
├── HMAC request signing for financial endpoints
├── Device fingerprinting
├── Anomaly detection alerts
├── Rate limit upgrade to Redis (Upstash)
└── Content Security Policy headers

Phase 3 (Ongoing):
├── Regular security audits
├── Penetration testing
├── Bug bounty program (post-launch)
└── SOC 2 Type I preparation
```

