## 🔐 Security Comparison — How We Stack Up

| Feature | PayWise (Current) | PayWise AI (Target) | CRED | Fi Money |
|---------|-------------------|---------------------|------|----------|
| RLS data isolation | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| Input validation | ✅ Double-layer | ✅ Triple-layer | ✅ | ✅ |
| Rate limiting | ✅ In-memory | ✅ Redis (Upstash) | ✅ | ✅ |
| Column-level encryption | ❌ | ✅ pgcrypto | ✅ | ✅ |
| Audit logging | ❌ | ✅ | ✅ | ✅ |
| DPDP Act compliance | ❌ | ✅ Full | Partial | ✅ |
| Data export/deletion | ❌ | ✅ API | Basic | ✅ |
| AI prompt injection protection | N/A | ✅ | N/A | N/A |
| Zero-trust API design | ✅ | ✅ Enhanced | ✅ | ✅ |
| Transaction data doesn't touch our servers | N/A | ✅ (client-side encrypt) | ❌ | ❌ |

**Our security advantage:** We NEVER process actual payments. We're an intelligence layer only. This means:
- No PCI-DSS compliance needed (we don't handle card numbers)
- No RBI payment aggregator license needed
- Lower regulatory burden = faster iteration
- Users trust us more = we're not touching their money

